President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed September 17 as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23 as Constitution Week. In the proclamation, President Biden emphasizes the importance of the Constitution in guiding the growth and progress of the United States. He recognizes the ongoing efforts to protect and expand the fundamental right to vote and emphasizes the commitment to fulfilling the promise of equality for all Americans. The proclamation also acknowledges the historical struggles and sacrifices made to uphold the principles of the Constitution. President Biden encourages the display of the flag of the United States on all government buildings during this period as a symbol of celebration and unity.